INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Resiliency and Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass, and the President to sign, legislation amending the Stafford Act to proactively fund the planning and construction of FEMA and HUD coastal resiliency projects.
EventItemMatterName: Amending the Stafford Act to proactively fund the planning and construction of FEMA and HUD coastal resiliency projects.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York to remove the name “Robert Moses” from various state parks, roadways and bridges in recognition of the racism that motivated specific characteristics of those venues and discouraged lower income New Yorkers, specifically people of color, from easily accessing them.
EventItemMatterName: Remove the name “Robert Moses” from various state parks, roadways and bridges.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Governor and the Chief Judge of the State of New York to implement appropriate COVID-19 safety protocols and improve the efficiency of criminal trials.
EventItemMatterName: Governor and the Chief Judge of the State of New York to implement appropriate COVID-19 safety protocols and improve the efficiency of criminal trials.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to early voting
EventItemMatterName: Early voting.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation the provision of financial grants to small businesses and non-profit organizations to be used for cleaning expenses
EventItemMatterName: Provision of financial grants to small businesses and non-profit organizations to be used for cleaning expenses.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation allowing local health departments to implement changes to improve the COVID-19 vaccine roll out.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing local health departments to implement changes to improve the COVID-19 vaccine roll out.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
